claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A portion of full prescribing information for Flublok (recombinant influenza vaccine), including a table of contents listing sections (Indications and Usage; Dosage and Administration; Contraindications; Warnings and Precautions; Adverse Reactions; Clinical Pharmacology; Clinical Studies; etc.) and text summarizing adverse reaction rates by age group (percentages of pain, headache, fatigue, muscle pain in adults 18–49, 50–64, and ≥65 years). does not support the claim because the image only presents adverse reaction frequencies and section headings, with no data comparing antibody responses between higher-dose recombinant and egg-based standard-dose vaccines Note: Image shows prescribing information and adverse event data only; immunogenicity or comparative efficacy data are not included
